'''
This project is an interactive night-sky explorer application with two modes, Learn mode 
and Game mode. 

In Learn mode, users can explore constellations by navigating between sky 
regions and hovering over constellations to preview their figures. Clicking on a constellation
reveals additional information, allowing for self-guided exploration and education. 

In Game mode, users are challenged to locate specific constellations within a time limit, 
and with certain constraints: 
Easy: 2 minutes, no penalties
Intermediate: 1.5 minutes, limited lives
Hard: 1 minute, restricted "telescope" vision, and limited lives

Core features: 
- Dynamic slide-based navigation
- Dual-mode architecture
- Interactive constellation detection
- Difficulty scaling with timers, lives, and vision constraints
- Real-time feedback system
- UI rendering using app variables

Grading Shortcuts:
Learning mode is pretty straightforward, so there are no shortcuts. Have fun exploring!
Game mode has three difficulties. At any point, you can press 'p' to pause, although this
is not part of the game itself. To view what happens when you "win" (i.e. find all the 
constellations in a given time), press the 'w' key. To find out what happens when you lose, 
press 'l'. To see features that lead to 'game over', you can set the difficulty to hard and 
wait for the timer to run out, or click on three incorrect constellations to lose all of 
your lives. 
'''
